## 11. Risks & Mitigations

| Risk | Likelihood | Mitigation |
|------|-----------|------------|
| ESMFold public API rate-limited or down | Medium | Cache all predictions; fall back to local ESMFold (slow but functional on 16GB RAM) |
| BLAST remote API slow for 100-variant benchmark | High | Use local BLAST+ with swissprot DB (~7GB download); run once, cache results |
| Claude API costs for 100-variant benchmark | Low | Estimate: ~$2–5 total at Sonnet pricing; acceptable |
| Agent calls tools in wrong order | Medium | System prompt specifies order explicitly; add order validation in tool dispatch |
| GB1 dataset experimental scores don't correlate with agent | Medium | This is a valid scientific finding — report it honestly with analysis of why |
| ESM-2 model weights too large for laptop RAM | Low | Use `esm2_t6_8M` (31MB) for development; `esm2_t12_35M` (150MB) for final benchmark |

---

## 12. Assumptions

- Anthropic API key available with Sonnet access
- Laptop has ≥ 16GB RAM (ESM-2 35M model requires ~2GB; ESMFold local requires ~16GB)
- Internet access for ESMFold API and BLAST remote (or local BLAST+ installed)
- TM-align binary downloadable from Zhang lab (free, no license)
- GB1 dataset publicly available via Supplement of Olson et al. 2014

---

## 13. Out of Scope

- De novo sequence generation (RFdiffusion, ProteinMPNN)
- Multi-chain or protein-protein interaction analysis
- Fine-tuning any foundation model
- User authentication or multi-user sessions
- Integration with wet lab ordering or ELN systems
- Support for DNA/RNA sequences

